.TH HUMAN 1 "March 2026" "human 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
human \- autonomous AI assistant runtime (C/ASM/WASM)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B human
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.PP
.B human
\fB--version\fR | \fB-v\fR
.PP
.B human
\fB--help\fR | \fB-h\fR
.PP
.B human
\fB--mcp\fR
.RB "(alias for " "mcp" " subcommand)"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B human
is a minimal C11 autonomous AI assistant runtime. It provides an agent loop,
tool execution, memory backends, security policies, and integrations for
multiple AI providers, channels, and hardware peripherals.
.PP
Built for minimal binary size and memory footprint with zero dependencies
beyond libc, optional SQLite, and libcurl.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B agent
Start interactive agent session (default if no command given).
.TP
.B gateway
Start webhook gateway server. See
.BR human-gateway (1)
for options.
.TP
.B mcp
Run as MCP server (stdin/stdout JSON-RPC).
.TP
.B service
Run as background service (daemonize).
.TP
.B service-loop
Run service loop in foreground.
.TP
.B status
Show runtime status.
.TP
.B onboard
Interactive setup wizard.
.TP
.B doctor
Run system diagnostics.
.TP
.B cron
Manage scheduled tasks (list, add, remove).
.TP
.B channel
Channel management (list, status, start, stop).
.TP
.B skills
Skill discovery and integration.
.RS
Subcommands: list, search, install, uninstall, update, info, publish.
.RE
.TP
.B hardware
Hardware peripheral management (list, info, scan, flash, monitor).
.TP
.B migrate
Migrate memory backends (e.g. sqlite to markdown).
.TP
.B memory
Memory operations (stats, count, list, search, get, forget).
.TP
.B workspace
Workspace management (show, set).
.TP
.B capabilities
Show available capabilities.
.TP
.B models
List available models.
.TP
.B auth
Authentication management (login, status, logout).
.TP
.B update
Check for updates.
.TP
.B version
Show version information.
.TP
.B help
Show help information.
.SH GLOBAL FLAGS
.TP
