.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is loaded from
.IR ~/.human/config.json .
.PP
Run
.B human onboard
for interactive setup, or create the config directory and file manually.
See the project documentation for schema and options.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HUMAN_PROVIDER
Default AI provider (e.g. openai, anthropic, ollama, gemini).
.TP
.B HUMAN_MODEL
Default model name.
.TP
.B HUMAN_API_KEY
Fallback API key when provider-specific keys are not set.
.TP
.B OPENAI_API_KEY
API key for OpenAI provider.
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
API key for Anthropic provider.
.TP
.B GEMINI_API_KEY
API key for Google Gemini provider.
.TP
.B OLLAMA_HOST
Ollama host URL (for ollama provider).
.TP
.B HUMAN_WORKSPACE
Workspace directory.
.TP
.B HUMAN_GATEWAY_HOST
Gateway bind address.
.TP
.B HUMAN_GATEWAY_PORT
Gateway port.
.TP
.B HUMAN_WEBHOOK_HMAC_SECRET
HMAC secret for webhook verification.
.TP
.B HUMAN_AUTONOMY
Autonomy level (0-4).
.TP
.B HUMAN_METACOGNITION
Enable or disable agent metacognition (bounded re-entry, SQLite history, follow-up labeling).
Values: 1/true/on or 0/false/off.
.TP
.B HUMAN_METACOG_MAX_REGEN
Maximum metacognition-driven regeneration passes per assistant turn (0-32).
.TP
.B HUMAN_LOG
Log file path for service/gateway.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.human/
Config directory (config.json, memory.db, etc.).
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/human
Typical install location (or ~/.local/bin if user install).
